M|rules|title: Use after() for Non-Blocking Operations
M|rules|impact: MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: faster rsp times
M|rules|tags: server, async, logging, anl, side-effects
M|rules|Use Next.js's `after()` to schedule work that should execute after a rsp is sent. This prevents logging, anl, and other side effects from blocking the rsp.
M|rules|**Incorrect (blocks rsp):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|import { logUserAction } from '@/app/utils'
M|rules|export async function POST(request: Request) {
M|rules|// Perform mutation
M|rules|await updateDatabase(request)
M|rules|// Logging blocks the rsp
M|rules|const userAgent = request.headers.get('user-agt') || 'unknown'
M|rules|await logUserAction({ userAgent })
M|rules|return new rsp(JSON.stringify({ status: 'success' }), {
M|rules|status: 200,
M|rules|headers: { 'cnt-Type': 'application/json' }
M|rules|})
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (non-blocking):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|import { after } from 'next/server'
M|rules|import { headers, cookies } from 'next/headers'
M|rules|import { logUserAction } from '@/app/utils'
M|rules|export async function POST(request: Request) {
M|rules|// Perform mutation
M|rules|await updateDatabase(request)
M|rules|// Log after rsp is sent
M|rules|after(async () => {
M|rules|const userAgent = (await headers()).get('user-agt') || 'unknown'
M|rules|const sessionCookie = (await cookies()).get('ses-id')?.value || 'anonymous'
M|rules|logUserAction({ sessionCookie, userAgent })
M|rules|})
M|rules|return new rsp(JSON.stringify({ status: 'success' }), {
M|rules|status: 200,
M|rules|headers: { 'cnt-Type': 'application/json' }
M|rules|})
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|The rsp is sent immediately while logging happens in the background.
M|rules|**Common use cases:**
M|rules|- anl tracking
M|rules|- Audit logging
M|rules|- Sending notifications
M|rules|- Cache invalidation
M|rules|- Cleanup tasks
M|rules|**Important notes:**
M|rules|- `after()` runs even if the rsp fails or redirects
M|rules|- Works in Server Actions, Route Handlers, and Server Components
M|rules|Reference: [https://nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/functions/after](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/functions/after)